        <section id="detailed_desc" deliveryTarget="details" otherprops="no-title">
            <p props="electron">After successfully registering this callback and starting audio and video stream recording, the SDK periodically triggers this callback based on the value you set for <codeph>recorderInfoUpdateInterval</codeph> in <xref keyref="MediaRecorderConfiguration"/>, reporting the current recording file's name, duration, and size.</p>
            <p props="rn">After successfully registering this callback and starting audio and video stream recording, the SDK periodically triggers this callback based on the value you set for <codeph>recorderInfoUpdateInterval</codeph> in <xref keyref="MediaRecorderConfiguration"/>, reporting the filename, duration, and size of the current recording file.</p>
            <p props="flutter">After successfully registering this callback and starting audio and video stream recording, the SDK periodically triggers this callback based on the value of <codeph>recorderInfoUpdateInterval</codeph> set in <xref keyref="MediaRecorderConfiguration"/>, reporting the current recording file name, duration, and size.</p>
            <p props="unity">After successfully registering this callback and starting audio and video stream recording, the SDK periodically triggers this callback based on the <codeph>recorderInfoUpdateInterval</codeph> value set in <xref keyref="MediaRecorderConfiguration"/>, reporting the current recording file name, duration, and size.</p>
